snippet.textDisplay:
Love'd the video and had some thoughts.


If you get another one of those try adding the peanut butter to the main. Half the red pepper and salt to taste. Eat off a whole cracker.


A FRH is basically just a mobile sous vide. They have to pre cook all that food before hand wonder how many of those meals are cooked in the poach via that method. In my experience traditional vegetarian dishes or pasta doesn't hold up well in that method of cooking.



why don't they send different packets of spices or ingredients (besides red/black pepper and salt) with those MRES in the accessory pack. Soldiers primary enemy is boredom and monotony. Maybe the improvement to meal fatigue and the ability to cook would be worth the weight and bulk.


Most of the story's I hear of people eating these are on base garrisoned/in a vehicle and not necessarily on foot or patrolling. My information is from anecdotal sources though. It'd be interesting to find out the primary place were there consumed at though.


I guess the culmination of those thoughts is if your a occupying force trying to fit the needs a diverse population why not issue more of a individual field kitchen instead of a personal meal. When we made the MRE concept we were fighting a different type of war. The conflict we fight now has more of a hurry up and wait kind of pacing. Maybe its time for the concept to take a new form.


I've been watching your videos for years. I don't know what it is but your content. But it genuinely makes my wife's and my day when you upload a video. Thank you.

snippet.textDisplay:
In all the MREs I've ever had, the peanut butter is so dry, there's no way it would ever squeeze out like that. Would only come out in a big blob. No matter how much you squish it around before opening.

The crackers are spot on. Dry and crumbly.

I miss the hashbrowns with bacon and the sausage patty breakfast MRE. Mixed together, that was an awesome breakfast.

I really like the tip about mixing the coffee into the chocolate protein drink. I'll have to try that one!
snippet.textOriginal:
In all the MREs I've ever had,  the peanut butter is so dry,  there's no way it would ever squeeze out like that.  Would only come out in a big blob. No matter how much you squish it around before opening. 

The crackers are spot on.  Dry and crumbly. 

I miss the hashbrowns with bacon and the sausage patty breakfast MRE. Mixed together,  that was an awesome breakfast. 

I really like the tip about mixing the coffee into the chocolate protein drink.  I'll have to try that one!
